Taita Taveta Governor John Mruttu is unfit for office because he is at the helm of a county "riddled with graft", Wundanyi MP Thomas Mwadeghu has said.He said county officials are not proactive about reverting land grabbed by foreigners to residents. &ldquo;I have not been bashing Mruttu for nothing. It&rsquo;s because he has failed to deliver and prove he worth being reelected,&rdquo; Mwadeghu said on Sunday.The MP plans to use the land agenda as his campaign tool as he seeks to be elected governor. Mwadeghu said Mruttu has failed to improve education standards.&ldquo;We were position 42 out of 47 in the recently released KCPE results. There has to be something wrong because this is miserable,&rdquo; he said.Mwadeghu urged the Taita community to unite and vote for him.Mruttu has denied graft allegations.